3.28.20  11:29 am   So I always feel like this universe was 'programmed' by something with some sort of imagination in a simpler, more logical universe. And I don't mean it in a crazy person way of "oh we were all made as part of it" but I mean that that they set all the the weird laws of physics as a 'code' with all particles and waves here being represented as data there and then let the Big Bang happen. And then the classic question from that would be "well who made their universe?" And then I'd think that it was 'programmed' in an even simpler and more logical universe that has the capacity to create a slightly more complex one and that it would keep going that way until you get to a universe that's a hypothetical idea, like an exact representation of logic. Does that make sense or is it too arrogantly trying to know everything?

     it's never arrogant to want to know everything. knowing things is awesome, and everything is all the things, at least that's the way it was advertised
